        "text": "People find bugs in bug complicated programs all the time, so I can’t agree with this binary characterization of the inutility of many eyeballs. OTOH I would say that many eyeballs turned out to be fairly unhelpful with architecture and UX problems, which are widespread in FOSS :pensive: (the complexity that bothers us all is usually the result of the architecture decisions rather than line by line coding errors)",
