        "client_msg_id": "317BC66F-A0D6-44F8-90CB-601B466E9B32",
        "text": "I'm struck that there hasn't yet been any mention of the source availability of every single website. Even with modern JS DX obsession, utility CSS, the node_modules black hole, bundling and minification and such obfuscating things to the point of FUBAR, I still _frequently_ pop open devtools and explore how sites are made, learn new techniques, steal assets, overcome user-hostile \"features\", etc.",
        "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
